Roll Number: MT25005
File Names

    Part A: MT25005_PartA_bash.sh, MT25005_PartA_Server.sh, MT25005_PartA_Client.sh

    Part B: MT25005_PartB_bash.sh, MT25005_PartB_Server.c, MT25005_PartB_Client.c

    Part C: MT25005_PartC_bash.sh

    Part D: MT25005_PartD_Plot.py

    Build: Makefile

How to Implement
1. Compile the Source Code

Run the make file to compile all C source files:
Bash

make

2. Setup Environment

Give execution permissions to the Part A bash script and run it:
Bash

chmod +x MT25005_PartA_bash.sh
./MT25005_PartA_bash.sh

3. Run Server and Client

You will need to use multiple terminals:

    Terminal 1 (Server): Execute the server in its namespace:
    Bash

    sudo ip netns exec ns_server ./ServerA 1 10

    Terminal 2 (Client): Execute the client in its namespace:
    Bash

    sudo ip netns exec ns_client ./ClientA 4096 10

4. Performance Profiling

In Terminal 3, immediately after starting the server, run the perf tool to monitor the server's process. Replace Pid with the actual PID of the server (found using pidof ServerA):
Bash

sudo perf stat -e cycles,L1-dcache-load-misses,LLC-load-misses,context-switches -p Pid

5. View Results

The perf command will display the performance results automatically once the server process terminates.